The White House has announced that Nancy Hogan will be stepping down from her position as Assistant to the President & Director of Presidential Personnel, and Jonathan McBride will take on the position. President Obama expressed gratitude to Hogan for her service and praised her for attracting talented public servants. McBride, who joined the administration in 2009, has experience in employer branding and media. He has also worked for Goldman Sachs and U.S. Senator Herb Kohl. McBride will now serve as Assistant to the President & Director of Presidential Personnel.